## 🤖 Machine Learning Models

### Linear Regression

Used as a baseline regression model.

### Random Forest Regressor

Used to capture complex relationships between features and house prices.

---

## 📈 Evaluation Metrics

- Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
- Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)
- R² Score
- Cross Validation Score

---

## 📷 Visualizations

- House Price Distribution
- Correlation Heatmap
- Actual vs Predicted Prices
- Feature Importance
- Income vs House Price
- Outlier Detection

---

## 🔍 Key Findings

- Median income was the most influential feature.
- Location significantly impacted house prices.
- Random Forest achieved better performance than Linear Regression.
- Housing prices depend on both economic and geographical factors.

---

## 💡 Business Recommendation

Real estate businesses should prioritize location and median income information while estimating property values. Machine learning models can help improve pricing accuracy and support better investment decisions.

